title: Falcon 9 Full Thrust
summary: Falcon 9 Full Thrust (also known as Falcon 9 v1.2, with variants Block 1 to Block 5) is a partially reusable medium-lift launch vehicle, designed and manufactured by SpaceX. Designed in 2014â€“2015, Falcon 9 Full Thrust began launch operations in December 2015. As of 2 December 2021, Falcon 9 Full Thrust had performed 110 launches without any failures. Based on the Lewis point estimate of reliability, this rocket is the most reliable orbital launch vehicle currently in operation.[8]
